
How do we run the code in our project?
go run main.go

GO CLI
	go run => Compile a bunch of go source code files, to run

	go build => Compiles a bunch of go source code files to a file

	go fmt => Formats all the code in each file in the current directory

	go install => Compiles and "installs" a package

	go get => Downloads the raw source code of someone else's package

	go test => Runs any test associated with the current project

What does 'package main' mean?

	package = project = workspace

	Types of Package

	Executable - Generates a file that we can run
			   - When it has main.go it is an executable project	
			   - Defines a func main

	Reusable - Code used as 'helpers'. Good place to put reusable logic

What does 'import fmt' mean?
	- Gives my package main, all the funcionality in fmt
	- fmt is a short of format, it is used to print

What's that 'func' thing?
	- func -> it is short for function
	- main -> name of the funcion

How is the main.go file organized?
	- package main  -> package declaration
	- import "fmt" -> import other packages that we need
	- func main -> declare functions, tell Go to do things
